# Fireplace shipped skills manifest
#
# These are the read-only, installer-owned skills shipped with Fireplace Agent.
# They use the reserved "fireplace-" directory prefix and are loaded via the
# config key skills.external_dirs: [ ${HERMES_HOME}/fireplace-skills ].
# The installer overwrites $FH/fireplace-skills wholesale on 'fireplace update';
# agent/user-authored skills (no "fireplace-" prefix) in $FH/skills are never
# touched. 'fireplace doctor' / update use this list to detect the shipped set.
#
# Format: <skill-dir-name> — <short description>

fireplace-api — Read the Fireplace MCP read tools effectively (markets, events, orderbook, candles, trader/wallet/smart-money reads, news, leaderboard, my_* account reads, order status).
fireplace-discover — Find markets worth betting on: mispricing/fish, smart-money accumulation, trending, catalyst, structural, personalized — each validated for tradeable liquidity, then ranked.
fireplace-research — Deep-dive one market into a thesis: resolution first, price & flow, holders both sides, news, term structure, synthesize a numeric fair value.
fireplace-news — Judge whether a news item actually moves a market, read against its exact resolution criteria; combines the Fireplace news layer with web_search.
fireplace-thesis — Turn research into a structured, falsifiable trade thesis (fair value, levels, mechanism, evidence, falsifier, manual-Kelly size).
fireplace-trading — Place, size, and reason about trades; orderbook-first, order-type selection, propose-and-confirm, gated execution tools (read-only by default).
fireplace-portfolio — Review the logged-in user's (or any trader's) portfolio: PnL, positions, open orders, historical PnL, unredeemed value, followed wallets; exposure, concentration, and a skill-vs-luck track-record read.
fireplace-risk — Risk management: pre-trade checklist, position sizing, orderbook depth (spread/walls/imbalance), concentration via open-interest/top-positions, stop orders, per-trade & portfolio limits.
fireplace-premortem — Red-team your own conclusion before committing to a money-moving recommendation; present the counter-case alongside the trade.
